"notes":"The app is the combination of BABY CRYING DETECTOR and VEHICLE MOVEMENT DETECTOR.
The sensors used are the analog MEMS microphone MP23ABS1, the LSM6DSOX MEMS accelerometer, gyroscope and the embedded Machine Learning Core.
The Baby crying app implements the AI processing and the FFT of audio signal to detect if a baby is crying using the microphone.
The MLC Vehicle movement recognition algorithm (MotionAR library) can recognize the movement of the vehicle by mechanical vibration of accelerometer and gyroscope.
The features have been used for MLC code generation are: MEAN-acc, VAR-acc, PeakToPeak-acc, MAX-acc, MEAN-gyro, VAR-gyro, PeakToPeak-gyro, MAX-gyro, MIN-gyro, ENERGY-gyro.
The combination of no adult in vehicle and baby is crying generates an alert on the smartphone.",
